First, let's find the union (A∪B) and the symmetric difference (A∆B) of sets A and B.

A = {1, 2, 3}
B = {2, 3, 4}

A∪B = {1, 2, 3, 4} (union of A and B)

A∆B = (A - B) ∪ (B - A) = {1, 4} (symmetric difference of A and B)

Now, let's find the symmetric difference of (A∪B) and (A∆B):

(A∪B) = {1, 2, 3, 4}
(A∆B) = {1, 4}

(A∪B)∆(A∆B) = ((A∪B) - (A∆B)) ∪ ((A∆B) - (A∪B))

(A∪B) - (A∆B) = {1, 2, 3, 4} - {1, 4} = {2, 3}
(A∆B) - (A∪B) = {1, 4} - {1, 2, 3, 4} = {}

(A∪B)∆(A∆B) = {2, 3} ∪ {} = {2, 3}

So, the symmetric difference of (A∪B) and (A∆B) is {2, 3}.
